# Environment Configuration

```env
# Database
DATABASE_URL=file:./prisma/dev.db

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=development

# Staff PIN (for demo, use plain text; in production, hash with bcryptjs)
STAFF_PIN=5555
```

## Production Setup

For production deployments:

1. Use a hashed PIN:
   ```javascript
   // Generate hash
   const hash = await bcryptjs.hash('your-pin', 10);
   console.log(hash);
   ```

2. Store in database:
   ```env
   DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost/checkin
   NODE_ENV=production
   ```

3. Enable HTTPS and set secure headers

## Docker Environment

Docker Compose automatically uses these settings from the service definition.
